overview: 'The user initiated the conversation seeking a significant aesthetic
  upgrade for their sleep questionnaire application, describing its current look
  as "okay, but a little donkey." The goal was to create a more calming,
  professional, and thematically appropriate interface. The approach involved a
  multi-step process: first, a comprehensive review of existing styles, followed
  by the implementation of a new sleep-themed color palette and custom utility
  classes. Key UI components like cards, checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and
  the progress bar were redesigned. The main questionnaire form and intro
  section received significant visual enhancements, including decorative
  backgrounds and feature cards. As the process unfolded, it was discovered that
  many other questionnaire sections and the report section still retained older,
  inconsistent styling and hardcoded colors. These were systematically updated
  to align with the new theme, ensuring a cohesive look across the entire
  application. Additionally, a React console error related to  values
  being passed to input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the
  component to safely handle such values. The outcome is a visually appealing
  and consistent application that better reflects its purpose.'
